{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/condref\/wait(mutex:)"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/wait(mutex:)"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/CondProtocol-Implementations"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"wait"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"MutexT","kind":"genericParameter"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"mutex"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"MutexT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"where","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"MutexT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol","text":"MutexProtocol","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib13MutexProtocolP"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When using condition variables, it is possible that a spurious wakeup"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"may occur (ie: ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_wait()"},{"text":" returns even though ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_cond_signal()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" was"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"not called).  It’s also possible that a stolen wakeup may occur.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This is when ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_signal()"},{"type":"text","text":" is called, but another thread acquires"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"mutex"},{"text":" before this thread and modifies the state of the program in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such a way that when "},{"code":"g_cond_wait()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is able to return, the expected"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"condition is no longer met.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For this reason, ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_cond_wait()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" must always be used in a loop.  See","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the documentation for ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"text":" for a complete example.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib12CondProtocolPAAE4wait5mutexyqd___tAA05MutexC0Rd__lF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib7CondRefV","symbolKind":"method","title":"wait(mutex:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"GLib","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"wait"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"MutexT"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"mutex"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"MutexT"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"role":"symbol"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Atomically releases "},{"code":"mutex","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and waits until "},{"code":"cond","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is signalled.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"When this function returns, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"mutex"},{"type":"text","text":" is locked again and owned by the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"calling thread.","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/CondRef/CondProtocol-Implementations":{"type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","u